usb: typec: rts5453: select Sky1 GPIO IRQ provider on ACPI

The RTS5453 ACPI nodes on Orion O6 carry their interrupt as a GpioInt
resource from the Sky1 Cadence GPIO controller. If the Type-C driver is
built in but GPIO_CADENCE is left unset or modular, ACPI cannot translate
the GPIO interrupt early enough and the I2C client is left deferred with
"rts5453h: cannot get irq".

Select the Sky1 GPIO IRQ provider and PDC irqchip for CIX ACPI builds so
the provider is present whenever the RTS5453 ACPI client is enabled.

---
diff --git a/drivers/usb/typec/Kconfig b/drivers/usb/typec/Kconfig
--- a/drivers/usb/typec/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/Kconfig
@@ -115,6 +115,8 @@ config TYPEC_RTS5453
 	depends on I2C
 	depends on TYPEC
 	select REGMAP_I2C
+	select GPIO_CADENCE if ACPI && ARCH_CIX
+	select SKY1_PDC if ACPI && ARCH_CIX
 	help
 	  Say Y or M here if your system has a Realtek RTS5453H USB Type-C
 	  Power Delivery controller. This controller handles USB PD negotiation,
